The paper discusses distributed transactions and databases, which are typically studied in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also focuses on data partitioning and transaction execution, which are key topics in the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The use of fast RDMA-enabled networks suggests that the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category may also be relevant. The paper also discusses optimizing for data contention, which is related to operating systems (cs.OS) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
